  "body": "With the changes of #7917 , the help text for `helm status` no longer shows the `revision` flag.\r\n\r\nMy guess is that this is caused because helm status creates its revision flag as a PersistentFlag:\r\nhttps://github.com/helm/helm/blob/3779d959667095e03308a2e49480748f7911b228/cmd/helm/status.go#L77\r\n\r\nHowever, the kubectl package used to group commands, I'm guessing shows persistent flags in a `helm <subcommand> options`.\r\n\r\nI think there is no need to use a persistent flag for `helm status --revision` (a persistent flag is a flag that is inherited by sub-commands).  Note that the `--revision` flags of the different `helm get` commands are not persistent.\r\n\r\nOutput of `helm version`:\r\nversion.BuildInfo{Version:\"v3.2+unreleased\", GitCommit:\"3779d959667095e03308a2e49480748f7911b228\", GitTreeState:\"clean\", GoVersion:\"go1.13.7\"}\r\n\r\n/cc @zgfh ",
